{"title_page": "Bhaskar Rao.", "text_new": "[[File:Mr._Bhaskar_Rao.jpg|thumb|216x216px|Mr. Bhaskar Rao (IPS)]]\n'''Bhaskar Rao''' (born 24 May 1964) is an Indian Police Service Officer from Bangalore, Karnataka <ref> https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/events/bangalore/bengaluru-commissioner-bhaskar-raos-instructions-to-his-team/articleshow/74884859.cms </ref>. He is the 33rd Commissioner of Police for Bangalore City, incumbent since 2nd of August, 2019 <ref> https://www.bcp.gov.in/ </ref>. He was born in Tamil Nadu but, his original ancestry is from Karnataka. He completed his higher studies from Bangalore University and is an IPS officer of Karnataka cadre \u2013 1990 batch. He has served in various challenging and important positions in the Police Department. He completed his basic training at Lalbahadur Shastri National Academy of Administration, Mussoorie and Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel National Police Academy, Hyderabad.\n\n== Early life ==\nBorn on 24th May 1964 at Nungambakkarm, Chennai, India, Bhaskar Rao was brought up in Karnataka. Bhaskar Rao did his early schooling in various parts of Bihar and Bengaluru. He has completed his Graduation from National College, Jayanagar with Psychology, Economics and, Sociology as optional subjects. He has completed his graduation and post-graduation with M.A in Economics from Bangalore University. He started his career as an Army officer later worked as a Lecturer in Economics at NMKRV Women\u2019s College, Bengaluru, and then as a Research Fellow at the Institute for Social and Economic Change. He joined the police department as Superintendent of Police and served in Mandya, Davanagere, Shimoga, Hubli, Dharwad, Coorg and, Bangalore Rural District. He was an active member of NCC (Armored Corp) and NSS (National Service Scheme) <ref> https://www.theprotector.in/meet-the-protector/ </ref>.\n\n== Family Background ==\nBhaskar Rao is the son of Sri R.S. Raghunath Rao and Smt. Shakunthala Rao. His father served as an Engineer-in-Chief with the Government of Bihar, and his mother worked as a teacher.\n\n== Positions held ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Sl no.\n!Position Held\n!Duration\n!Place\n|-\n|1\n|Commissioner of Police\n|Aug 2019 \u2013 Present\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|2\n|Additional Director General of Police, KSRP\n|Jan 2017 \u2013 02 Aug 2019\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|3\n|Additional Director General of Police, Crimes, Technical Services, Forensic lab and Canine squad\n|Jan 2016 \u2013 Dec 2016\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|4\n|Additional Director General of Police, Directorate civil rights enforcement\n|Jul 2015 \u2013 Dec 2015\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|5\n|Additional Director General of Police, State Crime record and Police IT\n|Jan 2015 \u2013 Jun 2015\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|6\n|Inspector-General of Police\n|May 2011 \u2013 Sep 2013\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|7\n|Commissioner, Member of & Karnataka pollution board,\n\nBoard member of Northwest Road Corporation. Chairman of State Transport Authority\n|Jul 2008 \u2013 May 2011\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|8\n|Commissioner of Police\n|Jun 2007 \u2013 Jan 2008\n|Mysuru Area, India\n|-\n|9\n|Director, Security Vigilance and Operations\n\nBoard member BMTC. KSRTC, India\n|Mar 2004 \u2013 May 2007\n|Mysuru Area, India\n|-\n|10\n|Deputy Commissioner of Police\n|July 2003 - Feb 2004\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|11\n|Managing Director\n\n[Karnataka State Electronics Development Corporation Limited, Bangalore]\n|Aug 2002 \u2013 Jun 2003\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|12\n|Superintendent of Police\n|Apr 2001 \u2013 Jul 2002\n|Bangalore Rural District\n|-\n|13\n|Superintendent of Police\n|Dec 1999 \u2013 April 2001\n|United Nations, Yugoslavia\n|-\n|14\n|Superintendent of Police\n|Sep 1996 \u2013 Nov 1999\n|Madikeri Area, Kodagu District, India\n|-\n|15\n|Deputy Commissioner of Police [Law and Order]\n|Mar 1994 \u2013 Sep 1996\n|Hubli- Dharwad City, India\n|-\n|16\n|Assistant Superintendent of Police\n|Mar 1993 \u2013 Feb 1994\n|Shivamoga Area, India\n|-\n|17\n|Assistant Superintendent of Police\n|Oct 1992 \u2013 Feb 1993\n|Davangere, India\n|}\n\n== Awards ==\n\n* Poorna Chandra Tejaswi Award in September 2017.\n\n* Awarded President\u2019s Police Medal for Distinguished Service in August 2015 <ref> http://pibphoto.nic.in/documents/rlink/2015/aug/p201581408.pdf</ref>.\n\n[[File:President\u2019s_Police_Medal_for_Distinguished_Service_in_August_2015.png|none|thumb|124x124px]]\n\n* Awarded President\u2019s Police Meda<nowiki/>l for Meritorious Service 2008 <ref> https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/Brave-police-officers-feted-with-medals/articleshow/3367500.cms </ref>.\n\n[[File:President\u2019s_Police_Medal_for_Meritorious_Service.png|none|thumb|127x127px|President\u2019s Police Medal for Meritorious Service]]\n\n* United Nation\u2019s Medal for Services rendered in War Territory of Kosovo, Former Yugoslavia \u2013 2000.\n\n[[File:United_Nation\u2019s_Medal_for_Services_rendered_in_War_Territory_of_Kosovo,_Former_Yugoslavia_\u2013_2000.png|none|thumb|130x130px|United Nation\u2019s Medal for Services rendered in War Territory]]\n\n* Numerous appreciation letters from Government and Director General & Inspector General of Police for specific, commendable tasks performed.\n\n== Notable Contributions ==\n\n* Efficiently handled the ''demand of separation of Coorg from Karnataka.''\n* Creation of Training Manual for newly created Kosovo Police Service with International Criminal Investigation Training Assistance Program (ICITAP), Department of Justice, USA at Vucitrn Police School, Pristina, Kosovo.\n* Confidence-building measures among American Companies post 9/11 held in Bangalore as a Superintendent of Police, Bangalore District.\n* Affected Transport Reforms for the issue of Driving Session, Electronic Driver Testing Track and vehicle Registration using Smart Cards and discontinuing RC books, as Commissioner for Transport.\n* Introduced, first-ever reservation of web-based Bus seat booking called \u2018''Any Where Any Time Advance Reservation''\u2019 (AWATAR) similar to Airline Seat Reservation system.\n* He was the one who introduced Volvo Fleet in Karnataka State Transport Undertaking.\n* He was responsible for Creation of ''Karnataka State Industrial Security Force''.\n* He was responsible for the strengthening of Karnataka Coastal Security Police\n* He was responsible for Conducting of 60th All India Police Duty Meet-2016 at Mysore in December 2016.\n* He completed a 1750 Kms. \u201cKarnataka Darshan\u201d a Cycle ride across Karnataka State to promote Communal Harmony, Sanitation, Confidence Building. He also was responsible to raise the morale of Policemen by promoting fitness.<ref> https://metrosaga.com/man-of-the-moment-10-things-to-know-about-the-bengaluru-city-police-commissioner-bhaskar-rao/ </ref>\n= References =\n<references />\n", "text_old": "= Bhaskar Rao =\n[[File:Mr._Bhaskar_Rao.jpg|thumb|216x216px|Mr. Bhaskar Rao (IPS)]]\nBhaskar Rao (24th May 1964 - Present) is an Indian Police Service Officer from Bangalore, Karnataka <ref> https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/events/bangalore/bengaluru-commissioner-bhaskar-raos-instructions-to-his-team/articleshow/74884859.cms </ref>. He is the 33rd Commissioner of Police for Bangalore City, incumbent since 2nd of August, 2019 <ref> https://www.bcp.gov.in/ </ref>. He was born in Tamil Nadu but, his original ancestry is from Karnataka. He completed his higher studies from Bangalore University and is an IPS officer of Karnataka cadre \u2013 1990 batch. He has served in various challenging and important positions in the Police Department. He completed his basic training at Lalbahadur Shastri National Academy of Administration, Mussoorie and Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel National Police Academy, Hyderabad.\n\n== Early life ==\nBorn on 24th May 1964 at Nungambakkarm, Chennai, India, Bhaskar Rao was brought up in Karnataka. Bhaskar Rao did his early schooling in various parts of Bihar and Bengaluru. He has completed his Graduation from National College, Jayanagar with Psychology, Economics and, Sociology as optional subjects. He has completed his graduation and post-graduation with M.A in Economics from Bangalore University. He started his career as an Army officer later worked as a Lecturer in Economics at NMKRV Women\u2019s College, Bengaluru, and then as a Research Fellow at the Institute for Social and Economic Change. He joined the police department as Superintendent of Police and served in Mandya, Davanagere, Shimoga, Hubli, Dharwad, Coorg and, Bangalore Rural District. He was an active member of NCC (Armored Corp) and NSS (National Service Scheme) <ref> https://www.theprotector.in/meet-the-protector/ </ref>.\n\n== Family Background ==\nBhaskar Rao is the son of Sri R.S. Raghunath Rao and Smt. Shakunthala Rao. His Father Sri Raghunath Rao served as an Engineer-in-Chief with the Government of Bihar, and his mother Smt. Shakunthala worked as a teacher.\n\n= Interests =\n[[File:Bhaskar_Rao_cycle.jpg|thumb|216x216px|Bhaskar Rao's Interest in Cycling.]]\nBhaskar Rao is interested in outdoor activities, especially cycling. He is a long-distance runner and has participated in many marathons such as: Standard Chartered Mumbai Marathon, Air Tel Delhi Half Marathon, Pondicherry Marathon, Bangalore Midnight Marathon, Kaveri Trail Half Marathon. He likes driving and other adventure sports. Bhaskar Rao is also an avid reader of self-improvement books. Being an environment lover and, promoter of Empowerment of Constables and Lower Rank Officers, he has identified himself with several developmental causes. \n\n= Positions held =\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Sl no.\n!Position Held\n!Duration\n!Place\n|-\n|1\n|Commissioner of Police\n|Aug 2019 \u2013 Present\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|2\n|Additional Director General of Police, KSRP\n|Jan 2017 \u2013 02 Aug 2019\n|Bengaluru Area, India\n|-\n|3\n|Additional Director General 