{"title_page": "Original Golden Hits, Vol. 2", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Original Golden Hits, Vol. 2\n| type         = compilation\n| artist       = [[Jerry Lee Lewis]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 1969\n| recorded     = [[Memphis, Tennessee|Memphis]]\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Rock and roll]], [[rockabilly]], [[country music|country]]\n| length       = 27:20\n| label        = [[Sun Record Company]]\n| producer     = [[Shelby Singleton]]\n| prev_title   = [[Original Golden Hits, Vol. 1]]\n| prev_year    = 1969\n| next_title   = [[Rockin' Rhythm and Blues]]\n| next_year    = 1969\n}}\n\n'''''Original Golden Hits, Vol. 2''''' is an album by [[Jerry Lee Lewis]] released on the [[Sun Record Company]] label in 1969. It is the sequel to ''Vol. 1'', also issued in 1969, and compiled many of Lewis's popular Sun sides. Following up on his recent successes on the country charts, ''Original Golden Hits, Vol. 2'' peaked at number 6 on the ''Billboard'' country albums chart.{{cn|date=February 2015}}\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| total_length = 27:20\n\n| title1       = Fools Like Me\n| writer1      = {{hlist|[[Jack Clement]]|Murphy Maddox}}\n| length1      = 2:53\n\n| title2       = Break-Up\n| writer2      = [[Charlie Rich]]\n| length2      = 2:37\n\n| title3       = [[Money (That's What I Want)|Money]]\n| writer3      = {{hlist|Janie Bradford|[[Berry Gordy, Jr.]]}}\n| length3      = 2:41\n\n| title4       = I'll Make It All Up to You\n| writer4      = \n| length4      = 3:03\n\n| title5       = [[Mean Woman Blues]]\n| writer5      = Claude Demetrius\n| length5      = 2:25\n\n| title6       = [[What'd I Say]]\n| writer6      = [[Ray Charles]]\n| length6      = 2:27\n\n| title7       = [[High School Confidential (Jerry Lee Lewis song)|High School Confidential]]\n| writer7      = {{hlist|Ron Hargrave|Jerry Lee Lewis}}\n| length7      = 2:29\n\n| title8  